## Description
The **Catalog **operator allows to substitute input data with the corresponding value in a catalog. The operator search for the input string in a key column in a catalog, defined in the configuration settings, and then outputs the value corresponding to the key value found.

> Note

For more information, see: [DT3 Catalog Component](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-catalog-component).

## **Input**
**Input**

**Data type**

**Description**

**in0**

String

The string that you want to find in a key column in the catalog

**inâ€¦**

String

N-th input node, containing the string that you want to find in a key column in the catalog

## Output
**Output**

**Data type**

**Description**

**&lt;&gt;Record**

String

The catalog value corresponding to the key found

If the operator cannot find a corresponding key value, the default string defined in the configuration settings is returned.

**&lt;&gt;K 1**

String

N-th output, containing the catalog value corresponding to the key found

## **Settings**
**![](data:image/png;base64,)** 

- In the **Inputs **section, click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add**) to add an input node to the list.

- In the **Catalogs **section:

Select the catalog that you want to use from the **Available catalogs **drop-down menu.

- In the **Inputs **table, **Keys **column, click on the cell corresponding to the required input and select the catalog key that you want to use.

- From the **Default value **drop-down menu, select the string that the operator will return if it cannot find any key values in the catalog.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Tip

Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add item**) at the bottom of the drop-down menu to add a custom value to the list, then click ![](data:image/png;base64,) to confirm.

- Click **Apply **to confirm.

## Special cases
In special cases, the operator behaves as follows:

**Case**

**Behavior**

**NULL input (no input)**

The operator considers a NULL input as an empty string. The system logs a warning event.

**Input with NULL value**

The operator considers an input with NULL value as an empty string. The system logs a warning event
